# Web UI structure rules

## One component per file

- **Rule**: A `.tsx` file should define **only one React component**.
- Avoid additional helper components/functions that return JSX inside the same file.
- If you need a sub-UI piece, extract it into its own file under `web/src/components/...`.

## Pages should be composition only

- `web/src/app/**/page.tsx` should generally be **composition-only**:
  - import components
  - render layout
  - avoid defining extra JSX-returning functions inside the page file

## Shared UI primitives

- Use small primitives in `web/src/components/ui/*` (Button/Card/Container/etc.)
- Keep styling consistent (neutral enterprise palette + `dark:` variants)

